{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Waiting for a donated organ is a long shot, and buying one is illegal. But sophisticated software, combined with old-fashioned selflessness, could be a solution.", "abstract": "Software program offered through company BiologicTx allows people in need of kidney transplants and willing donors to form kidney-transplant chains where organs are swapped around to create best donor-recipient matches; sale of kidneys is banned in United States, but joining conventional donor wait list can result in years of delays before safe match is found; donor chains, founded on altruism, represent what economists call matching market.", "section_name": "Magazine", "print_page": "54", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Malia", "role": "reported", "lastname": "WOLLAN", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By MALIA WOLLAN"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/05/03/magazine/the-great-american-kidney-swap.html", "lead_paragraph": "Waiting for a donated organ is a long shot, and buying one is illegal. But sophisticated software, combined with old-fashioned selflessness, could be a solution.", "headline": {"main": "The Great American Kidney Swap", "content_kicker": "The Money Issue", "print_headline": "Pay It Forward"}, "_id": "55420b3a38f0d81c154895bb", "word_count": "1360", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/05/03/magazine/03kidney_ss-slide-U201/03kidney_ss-slide-U201-thumbWide-v2.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/05/03/magazine/03kidney_ss-slide-U201/03kidney_ss-slide-U201-thumbWide-v2.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 349, "url": "images/2015/05/03/magazine/03kidney_ss-slide-U201/03kidney_ss-slide-U201-articleLarge-v2.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/05/03/magazine/03kidney_ss-slide-U201/03kidney_ss-slide-U201-articleLarge-v2.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "349"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width